Many designs, posters, songs and video films have been [created
](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2009/06/30/iran-protest-movement-inspires-
art/)by Iranians and non-Iranians worldwide in support of Iran's “green”
protest movement against the [June 12 presidential election
results](../specialcoverage/iranian-election-2009/). Animators too, have
declared war on the dictatorship in Iran.

**Green People is an animation inspired
by[Gandhi](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohandas_Karamchand_Gandhi)**

**Mahmoud Ahmadinejad in 2009 election debate**

**Baha'i human rights**

Another animation reminds us that the Islamic Regime has repressed people for
years before the election.
[MideastYouth.com](http://www.youtube.com/user/MEYmedia) presents an animation
about the persecution of followers of the
[Bahai](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bah%C3%A1' data-versionurl=) faith in
Iran. A 30 year story.

